Newes from Spaine The king of Spaines edict, for the expulsion & banishment of more then nine hundred thousand Moores out of his kingdome, which conspired and plotted to bring the kingdome of Spaine vnder the power and subiection of the Turkes and Saracens. Translated out of Spanish into English by W.I. Proclamations. 1611. English Spain. Sovereign (1598-1621 : Philip III) W. I., fl. 1611.
[14] p.
[By E. Allde] for Nathaniel Butter, and are to be solde at his shop at the signe of the pide-Bull neere St. Austins gate, Imprinted at London : 1611.
Printer's name from STC. Identified as STC 22995 on UMI microfilm reel 729. Signatures: A⁴ (-A1) B⁴. Formerly STC 22995. Some print show-through; pages stained. Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
